article.description: Nykesha Sales scored 25 of her career high-tying 29 points in the second half and the Orlando Miracle rallied to beat the slumping New York Liberty 77-65 for their fourth straight win Sunday.
article.headline: Sales scores 25 in second-half Miracle rally
article.linkText: Miracle score 52 in second half to down Liberty
article.story:
ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Nykesha Sales scored 25 of her career high-tying 29 points in the second half and the Orlando Miracle rallied to beat the slumping New York Liberty 77-65 for their fourth straight win Sunday. Shannon Johnson added 17 points, 14 after halftime, and nine rebounds for the Miracle. She made 12 of 15 free throws, both career highs. Orlando's 52-point second half was its season best, as was its 19 free throws after the break. The Miracle's 7-3 start is the best in the franchise's four seasons. New York, losers of three straight and four of its last five, got 16 points and eight rebounds from Tari Phillips. Vickie Johnson scored 12 of her 13 points after halftime, while Crystal Robinson and Tamika Whitmore each added 12. Orlando trailed 45-34 with 13:48 remaining, but erased the deficit in 87 seconds. The Miracle made seven free throws in the comeback, and tied the game at 45 as Johnson completed a three-point play and hit a pair of foul shots. The Miracle then took an eight-point lead, 56-48, behind 3-pointers from Adrienne Johnson, Sales and Shannon Johnson on consecutive possessions. Vickie Johnson hit a long jumper and a 3-pointer to bring the Liberty within five points with 2:43 to go. But the Miracle reeled off seven straight points, including a 3-point play by Sales, to seal the win. New York's trapping defense stymied Orlando from the start, as the Miracle missed their first nine shots. For the half, the Miracle shot 25 percent (7-for-28) and scored 23 points -- both season lows. The Liberty broke ahead late in the first half behind a 13-2 run, with Robinson scoring five points and Phillips adding four. During that 6:19 stretch, Orlando missed seven straight shots and trailed by seven at intermission.

Game notes
New York reserve center Sue Wicks sprained her right ankle midway through the second half and didn't return. She had six points and six rebounds in nine minutes. ... This was Orlando's only home game in a stretch of seven contests, but the Miracle have won four in a row on the road.
